just_use __init__.py

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: rules package re-exports

Re-exports the public surface of the `rules/` subpackage so
callers can write `from rules import classify, neighbors,
RED, ...` without caring which sub-module a symbol lives in.

## Status

- Mirrors the convention used by `games/lynrummy/elm/src/Game/Rules/`
  — sub-modules per concern (`Card`, `StackType`), single
  entry point per layer.
- Created on the Class-1/2 segregation migration.

## Pointers

- `rules/card.py` — card primitives.
- `rules/stack_type.py` — classification + rule predicates.
